&lt;h2&gt;


Bundle Size: The Part I'm Proudest Of
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The core engine is &lt;strong&gt;under 3 kB&lt;/strong&gt; gzipped. Zero dependencies.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class="highlight js-code-highlight"&gt;
&lt;pre class="highlight shell"&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class="nv"&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;npm &lt;span class="nb"&gt;install &lt;/span&gt;featuredrop
added 1 package &lt;span class="k"&gt;in &lt;/span&gt;0.4s
0 vulnerabilities
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;



&lt;p&gt;Everything uses subpath exports for tree-shaking:&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class="highlight js-code-highlight"&gt;
&lt;pre class="highlight javascript"&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;// Only imports what you use&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="k"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;isNew&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;from&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="dl"&gt;'&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s1"&gt;featuredrop&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="dl"&gt;'&lt;/span&gt;           &lt;span class="c1"&gt;// ~1 kB&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="k"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;NewBadge&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;from&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="dl"&gt;'&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s1"&gt;featuredrop/react&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="dl"&gt;'&lt;/span&gt;   &lt;span class="c1"&gt;// ~3 kB&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="k"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;Tour&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;from&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="dl"&gt;'&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s1"&gt;featuredrop/react&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="dl"&gt;'&lt;/span&gt;       &lt;span class="c1"&gt;// ~4 kB&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;



&lt;p&gt;For comparison, enterprise adoption tools ship 100–300 kB of&lt;br&gt;
JavaScript to your users. FeatureDrop's entire React bundle is&lt;br&gt;
smaller than most tools' loading spinner GIF.&lt;/p&gt;
